      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming motor without spinning blades is a classic sign of a problem with the motor itself or the capacitor. It's likely that the motor is trying to run, but the capacitor is not providing the necessary spark to make the motor turn. I'd recommend turning off the power to the unit at the circuit breaker before attempting to inspect it, as a short circuit could be hazardous. \n\nYou'll also want to check the capacitor for any signs of damage, corrosion, or wear. If it's old or has been exposed to water, it may be the culprit. Take a close look at the motor's electrical connections and make sure they're clean and secure. If you're not comfortable with DIY repairs or if the issue persists after checking these, it's best to call a professional.",
